We have completed the implementation of the upgraded **Demo Mode** targeting focused **Computer Control** and **Browser Control** actions. Clicking the **Demo Mode** button in the sidebar now lets the operator run a tailored suite of browser and computer control demos or the full suite of autonomous capabilities.

## 🚀 Changes Accomplished

### 🧠 Backend updates
1. **[demonstration-engine.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/runtime/demonstration-engine.ts)**:
   - Modified `start(answers, categories)` to accept a list of categories.
   - Filtered active demos dynamically by checking `categories.includes(d.category)` to execute only relevant demos.
2. **[dashboard-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts)**:
   - Updated the `POST /api/demo/start` route to parse and pass `categories` to the runtime engine.

